#: ../../source/ambd_arduino/examples/peripheral/Flash Memory - Use Flash Memory Larger Than 4K.rst:47
msgid "Use ``readWord()`` to read the value stored in a memory address. In the example, we read the value stored in memory offset 0x3F00, that is 0xFC000 + 0x3F00 = 0xFFF00. ``readWord()`` function reads a 32-bit value and returns it."
msgstr ""

